def: Assigning the species of a general term.

Beads made of shells, used by the North American Indians asmoney, and also wrought into belts, etc., as an ornament.Round his waist his belt of wampum. Longfellow.Girded with his wampum braid. Whittier.
Quality or state of being mellow.
Not transitive; not passing over tas, an intransitive verb, e.g., the bird flies; the dog runs.
A woman's broad-brimmed hat of a form thought to resemble thoseshown in portraits by Thomas Gainsborough, the English artist (1727-88).
